Title: Object: Marquis of Dalhousie, late Colonel of the 26th Cameronians.
Description: Portrait of James Andrew Ramsay, Marquess of Dalhousie, bust-length to left, looking to front, wearing sash over military uniform; below, regimental badge, flanked by two soldiers, holding flags, standing on ornamental scrolls. Lithograph with hand-colouring
Bibliographic references: O'Donoghue 1908-25 / Catalogue of Engraved British Portraits preserved in the Department of Prints and Drawings in the British Museum (1) (Supplement)
Associated names: Portrait of: George Ramsay, 9th Earl Dalhousie
